expansion.name_gatherer: Phyrexia: All Will Be One Commander
expansion.name_tcgp: Commander: Phyrexia: All Will Be One
expansion.name_mkm: Commander: Phyrexia: All Will Be One

cards.name: Ixhel, Scion of Atraxa
cards.text:
Flying, vigilance, toxic 2
Corrupted - At the beginning of your end step, each opponent who has three or more poison counters exiles the top card of their library face down. You may look at and play those cards for as long as they remain exiled, and you may spend many as though it were mana of any color to cast those spells.

cards.name: Neyali, Suns' Vanguard
cards.text:
Attacking tokens you control have double strike.
Whenever one or more tokens you control attack a player, exile the top card of your library. During any turn you attacked with a token, you may play that card.

cards.name: Otharri, Suns' Glory
cards.text:
Flying, lifelink, haste
Whenever Otharri, Suns' Glory attacks, you get an experience counter. Then create a 2/2 red Rebel creature token that's tapped and attacking for each experience counter you have.
{2}{R}{W}, Tap an untapped Rebel you control: Return Otharri from your graveyard to the battlefield tapped.

cards.name: Vishgraz, the Doomhive
cards.text:
Menace, toxic 1 (Players dealt combat damage by this creature also get a poison counter.)
When Vishgraz, the Doomhive enters the battlefield, create three 1/1 colorless Phyrexian Mite artifact creature tokens with toxic 1 and "This creature can't block."
Vishgraz gets +1/+1 for each poison counter your opponents have.

cards.name: Clever Concealment
cards.text:
Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)
Any number of target nonland permanents you control phase out. (Treat them and anything attached to them as though they don't exist until your next turn.)

cards.name: Glimmer Lens
cards.text:
For Mirrodin! (When this Equipment enters the battlefield, create a 2/2 red Rebel creature token, then attach this to it.)
Whenever equipped creature and at least one other creature attack, draw a card.
Equip {1}{W}

cards.name: Kemba's Banner
cards.text:
For Mirrodin! (When this Equipment enters the battlefield, create a 2/2 red Rebel creature token, then attach this to it.)
Equpped creature gets +1/+1 for each creature you control.
Equip {2}{W}

cards.name: Norn's Choirmaster
cards.text:
Flying, first strike
Whenever a commander you control enters the battlefield or attacks, proliferate. (Choose any number of permanents and/or players, then give each another counter kind of each kind they already have.)

cards.name: Norn's Decree
cards.text:
Whenever one or more creatures an opponent controls deal combat damage to you, that player gets a poison counter.
Whenever a player attacks, if one or more players being attacked are poisoned, the attacking player draws a card.

cards.name: Staff of the Storyteller
cards.text:
When Staff of the Storyteller enters the battlefield, create a 1/1 white Spirit creature token with flying.
Whenever you create one or more creature tokens, put a story counter on Staff of the Storyteller.
{W}, {T}, Remove a story counter from Staff of the Storyteller: Draw a card.

cards.name: Geth's Summons
cards.text:
Return up to one target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
Corrupted - For each opponent who has three or more poison counters as you cast this spell, put up to one target creature card from that player's graveyard onto the battlefield under your control.

cards.name: Phyresis Outbreak
cards.text: Each opponent gets a poison counter. Then each creature your opponents control get -1/-1 for each poison counter its controller has.
cards.flavor:
"It is amusing that the fleshlings believe we are at war. In truth, they are nothing but scurrying pests to be eradicated."
-Azax-Azog, the Demon Thane

cards.name: Goldwardens' Gambit
cards.text:
Affinity for Equipment (This spell costs {1} less to cast for each Equipment you control.)
Create five 2/2 red Rebel creature tokens. They gain haste until end of turn. For each of those tokens, you may attach an Equipment you control to it.
cards.flavor: At Neyali's command, they took position. At Otharri's signal, theys truck.

cards.name: Hexplate Wallbreaker
cards.text:
For Mirrodin! (When this Equipment enters the battlefield, create a 2/2 red Rebel creature token, then attach this to it.)
Equipped creature gets +2/+2.
Whenver equipped creature attacks, if it's the first combat phase of the turn, untap each attacking creature. After this phase, there is an additional combat phase.
Equip {3}{R}

cards.name: Roar of Resistance
cards.text:
Creature tokens you control have haste.
Whenever one or more creatures attack, you may pay {1}{R}. If you do, creatures attacking your opponents and/or planeswalkers they control get +2/+0 until end of turn.

cards.name: Vulshok Factory
cards.text:
{T}: Add {R}. Put a charge counter on Vulshok Factory.
{2}{R}, {T}, Sacrifice Vulshok Factory: Create an X/X colorless Golem artifact creature token with haste, where X is the number of charge counters on Vulshok Factory. Activate only as a sorcery.

cards.name: Contaminant Grafter
cards.text:
Trample, toxic 1
Whenever one or more creatures you control deal combat damage to one or more players, proliferate.
Corrupted - At the beginning of your end step, if an opponent has three or more poison counters, draw a card, then you may put a land card from your hand onto the battlefield.

cards.name: Glissa's Retriever
cards.text:
Haste, toxic 3 (Players dealt combat damage by this creature also get three poison counters.)
Glissa's Retriever can't be blocked by creatures with power 2 or less.
Corrupted - When Glissa's Retriever dies, exile it. When you do, return up to X target cards from your graveyard to your hand, where X is the number of opponents who have three or more poison counters.

cards.name: Wurmquake
cards.text:
Corrupted - Create an X/X green Phyrexian Wurm creature token with trample and toxic 1, where X is the amount of mana spent to cast this spell. Then for each opponent with three or more poison counters, you create another one of those tokens.
Flashback {8}{G}{G} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

cards.name: Glistening Sphere
cards.text:
Glistening Sphere enters the battlefield tapped.
When Glistening Sphere enters the battlefield, proliferate.
{T}: Add one mana of any color.
Corrupted - {T}: Add three mana of any one color. Activate only if an opponent has three or more poison counters.

cards.name: Battle Screech
cards.text:
Create two 1/1 white Bird creature tokens with flying.
Flashback-Tap three untapped white creatures you control. (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

cards.name: Call the Coppercoats
cards.text:
Strive - This spell costs {1}{W} more to cast for each target beyond the first.
Choose any number of target opponents. Create X 1/1 white Human Soldier creature tokens, where X is the number of creatures those opponents control.
cards.flavor: When the alarm crystals flash, Drannith's finest answer the call.

cards.name: Collective Effort
cards.text:
Escalate-Tap an untapped creature you control. (Pay this cost for each mode chosen beyond the first.)
Choose one or more -
• Destroy target creature with power 4 or greater.
• Destroy target enchantment.
• Put a +1/+1 counter on each creature target player controls.

cards.name: Court of Grace
cards.text:
When Court of Grace enters the battlefield, you become the monarch.
At the beginning of your upkeep, create a 1/1 white Spirit creature token with flying. If you're the monarch, create a 4/4 white Angel creature token with flying instead.
cards.flavor: A righteous sovereign makes for a blessed realm.

cards.name: Cut a Deal
cards.text: Each opponent draws a card, then you draw a card for each opponent who drew a card this way.
cards.flavor:
"Abandon your selfish ambitions and become one with the Flesh Singularity."
-Elesh Norn

cards.name: Elspeth Tirel
cards.text:
[+2]: You gain 1 life for each creature you control.
[−2]: Create three 1/1 white Soldier creature tokens.
[−5]: Destroy all other permanents except for lands and tokens.

cards.name: Emeria Angel
cards.text:
Flying
Landfall - Whenever a land enters the battlefield under your control, you may create a 1/1 white Bird creature token with flying.
cards.flavor: When the earth shudders, the sky overflows.

cards.name: Felidar Retreat
cards.text:
Landfall - Whenever a land enters the battlefield under your control, choose one -
• Create a 2/2 white Cat Beast creature token.
• Put a +1/+1 counter on each creature you control. Those creatures gain vigilance until end of turn.

cards.name: Finale of Glory
cards.text: Create X 2/2 white Soldier creature tokens with vigilance. If X is 10 or more, also create X 4/4 white Angel creature tokens with flying and vigilance.
cards.flavor: The sky boiled over the citadel, dire and dark. Then the angels brought the dawn.

cards.name: Flawless Maneuver
cards.text:
If you control a commander, you may cast this spell without paying its mana cost.
Creatures you control gain indestructible until end of turn.
cards.flavor:
"Captain, your units are the tip of our spear. There is zero room for failure."
-Jirina Kudro

cards.name: Fumigate
cards.text: Destroy all creatures. You gain 1 life for each creature destroyed this way.
cards.flavor:
"Ghirapur's gremlin population poses a threat to the infrastructure of the fairgrounds. Threats must be eliminated."
-Sram, senior edificer

cards.name: Generous Gift
cards.text: Destroy target permanent. Its controller creates a 3/3 green Elephant creature token.
cards.flavor: The best presents are impossible to regift.

cards.name: Ghostly Prison
cards.text: Creatures can't attack you unless their controller pays {2} for each creature they control that's attacking you.
cards.flavor: Though the spirits' bodies were ethereal, Agnur soon learned that their blades were quite solid-and razor-sharp.

cards.name: Goldnight Commander
cards.text: Whenever another creature enters the battlefield under your control, creatures you control get +1/+1 until end of turn.
cards.flavor: "One faith, but many hands in victory."

cards.name: Grateful Apparition
cards.text:
Flying
Whenever Grateful Apparition deals combat damage to a player or planeswalker, proliferate. (Choose any number of permanents and/or players, then give each another counter of each kind already there.)

cards.name: Harmonious Archon
cards.text:
Flying
Non-Archon creatures have base power and toughness 3/3.
When Harmonious Archon enters the battlefield, create two 1/1 white Human creature tokens.
cards.flavor: First among equals.

cards.name: Hour of Reckoning
cards.text:
Convoke (Your creatures can help cast this spell. Each creature you tap while casting this spell pays for {1} or one mana of that creature's color.)
Destroy all nontoken creatures.
cards.flavor: Those who are chosen do not doubt. Those who remain do not lament.

cards.name: Increasing Devotion
cards.text:
Create five 1/1 white Human creature tokens. If this spell was cast from a graveyard, create ten of those tokens instead.
Flashback {7}{W}{W} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

cards.name: Intangible Virtue
cards.text: Creature tokens you control get +1/+1 and have vigilance.

cards.name: Mace of the Valiant
cards.text:
Equipped creature gets +1/+1 for each charge counter on Mace of the Valiant and has vigilance.
Whenever a creature enters the battlefield under your control, put a charge counter on Mace of the Valiant.
Equip {3}

cards.name: Martial Coup
cards.text: Create X 1/1 white Soldier creature tokens. If X is 5 or more, destroy all other creatures.
cards.flavor: Their war forgotten, the nations of Bant stood united in the face of a common threat.

cards.name: Maul of the Skyclaves
cards.text:
When Maul of the Skyclaves enters the battlefield, attach it to target creature you control.
Equipped creature gets +2/+2 and has flying and first strike.
Equip {2}{W}{W}

cards.name: Mentor of the Meek
cards.text: Whenever another creature with power 2 or less enters the battlefield under your control, you may pay {1}. If you do, draw a card.

cards.name: Midnight Haunting
cards.text: Create two 1/1 white Spirit creature tokens with flying.
cards.flavor: The path back to the world of the living is murky and bewildering. A geist may not even realize that it's terrifying its own loved ones.

cards.name: Norn's Annex
cards.text:
({W/P} can be paid with either {W} or 2 life.)
Creatures can't attack you or planeswalkers you control unless their controller pays {W/P} for each of those creatures.

cards.name: Path to Exile
cards.text: Exile target creature. Its controller may search their library for a basic land card, put that card onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.

cards.name: Phantom General
cards.text: Creature tokens you control get +1/+1.
cards.flavor: After his death, the general was reunited with fallen soldiers from over thirty of his campaigns.

cards.name: Phyrexian Rebirth
cards.text: Destroy all creatures, then create an X/X colorless Phyrexian Horror artifact creature token, where X is the number of creatures destroyed this way.
cards.flavor: As long as one drop of the oil exists, the joyous work continues.

cards.name: Prava of the Steel Legion
cards.text:
As long as it's your turn, creature tokens you control get +1/+4.
{3}{W}: Create a 1/1 white Soldier creature token.
Partner (You can have two commanders if both have partner.)

cards.name: Silverwing Squadron
cards.text:
Flying, vigilance
Silverwing Squadron's power and toughness are each equal to the number of creatures you control.
Whenever Silverwing Squadron attacks, create a number of 2/2 white Knight creature tokens with vigilance equal to the number of opponents you have.

cards.name: Swords to Plowshares
cards.text: Exile target creature. Its controller gains life equal to its power.
cards.flavor: "The arc of my blade has carved a path of light for the peace that will follow."

cards.name: White Sun's Zenith
cards.text: Create X 2/2 white Cat creature tokens. Shuffle White Sun's Zenith into its owner's library.
cards.flavor: After the Battle of Liet Field, the white sun crested above Taj-Nar, bringing hope to all who survived the carnage.

cards.name: Windborn Muse
cards.text:
Flying
Creatures can't attack you unless their controller pays {2} for each creature they control that's attacking you.
cards.flavor:
"Her voice is justice, clear and relentless."
-Akroma, angelic avenger

cards.name: Caress of Phyrexia
cards.text: Target player draws three cards, loses 3 life, and gets three poison counters.
cards.flavor: "I am weak. Make . . . me . . . ideal."

cards.name: Ichor Rats
cards.text:
Infect (This creature deals damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters and to players in the form of poison counters.)
When Ichor Rats enters the battlefield, each player gets a poison counter.

cards.name: Night's Whisper
cards.text: You draw two cards and you lose 2 life.
cards.flavor:
"I have seen things that would reduce a weaker person to blubbering and raving. Want to hear about them?"
-Vraska

cards.name: Painful Truths
cards.text: Converge - You draw X cards and you lose X life, where X is the number of colors of mana spent to cast this spell.
cards.flavor: As the Eldrazi spread, no secret that could give Zendikar's defenders an advantage was considered too dangerous to seek.

cards.name: Plague Stinger
cards.text:
Flying
Infect (This creature deals damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters and to players in the form of poison counters.)
cards.flavor: It leaves its victims one sting closer to phyresis.

cards.name: Chain Reaction
cards.text: Chain Reaction deals X damage to each creature, where X is the number of creatures on the battlefield.
cards.flavor:
"We train for the improbable, like lightning striking the same place twice, or striking everywhere at once."
-Nundari, Sea Gate militia captain

cards.name: Dragonmaster Outcast
cards.text: At the beginning of your upkeep, if you control six or more lands, create a 5/5 red Dragon creature token with flying.
cards.flavor: "This world will be ruled by its rightful sovereigns, not these hideous pretenders."

cards.name: Hate Mirage
cards.text: Choose up to two target creatures you don't control. For each of those creatures, create a token that's a copy of that creature. Those tokens gain haste. Exile them at the beginning of the next end step.
cards.flavor: Each monstrosity that fails to kill him expands his conjured arsenal.

cards.name: Hordeling Outburst
cards.text: Create three 1/1 red Goblin creature tokens.
cards.flavor:
"Leave no scraps, lest you attract pests."
-Mardu threat

cards.name: Legion Warboss
cards.text:
Mentor (Whenever this creature attacks, put a +1/+1 counter on target attacking creature with lesser power.)
At the beginning of combat on your turn, create a 1/1 red Goblin creature token. That token gains haste until end of turn and attacks this combat if able.

cards.name: Loyal Apprentice
cards.text:
Haste
Lieutenant - At the beginning of combat on your turn, if you control your commander, create a 1/1 colorless Thopter artifact creature token with flying. That token gains haste until end of turn.
cards.flavor: Those with knowledge are wise to listen to those with imagination.

cards.name: Siege-Gang Commander
cards.text:
When Siege-Gang Commander enters the battlefield, create three 1/1 red Goblin creature tokens.
{1}{R}, Sacrifice a Goblin: Siege-Gang Commander deals 2 damage to any target.
cards.flavor: "Ready . . . uh . . . fire!"

cards.name: Beast Within
cards.text: Destroy target permanent. Its controller creates a 3/3 green Beast creature token.
cards.flavor:
"Kill the weak so they can't drag the strong down to their level. This is true compassion."
-Benzir, archdruid of Temple Might

cards.name: Blight Mamba
cards.text:
Infect (This creature deals damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters and to players in the form of poison counters.)
{1}{G}: Regenerate Blight Mamba.
cards.flavor: Its venom drips with Phyrexia's hate.

cards.name: Carrion Call
cards.text: Create two 1/1 green Phyrexian Insect creature tokens with infect. (They deal damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters and to players in the form of poison counters.)
cards.flavor: The natural order is out of order.

cards.name: Cultivate
cards.text: Search your library for up to two basic land cards, reveal those cards, put one onto the battlefield tapped and the other into your hand, then shuffle.
cards.flavor: All seeds share a common bond, calling to each other across infinity.

cards.name: Evolution Sage
cards.text: Landfall - Whenever a land enters the battlefield under your control, proliferate. (Choose any number of permanents and/or players, then give each another counter of each kind already there.)
cards.flavor: "To care for yourself, cultivate the world. To care for the world, cultivate yourself."

cards.name: Mycosynth Fiend
cards.text: Mycosynth Fiend gets +1/+1 for each poison counter your opponents have.
cards.flavor:
"I wish I could take credit for it, but nature progresses on its own, just the way it should."
-Vorinclex, Voice of Hunger

cards.name: Noxious Revival
cards.text:
({G/P} can be paid with either {G} or 2 life.)
Put target card from a graveyard on top of its owner's library.
cards.flavor:
"Dead or alive, my creations are stronger than Jin-Gitaxias's septic minions."
-Vorinclex, Voice of Hunger

cards.name: Phyrexian Swarmlord
cards.text:
Infect (This creature deals damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters and to players in the form of poison counters.)
At the beginning of your upkeep, create a 1/1 green Phyrexian Insect creature token with infect for each poison counter your opponents have.

cards.name: Scavenging Ooze
cards.text: {G}: Exile target card from a graveyard. If it was a creature card, put a +1/+1 counter on Scavenging Ooze and you gain 1 life.
cards.flavor: In nature, not a single bone or scrap of flesh goes to waste.

cards.name: Viridian Corrupter
cards.text:
Infect (This creature deals damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters and to players in the form of poison counters.)
When Viridian Corrupter enters the battlefield, destroy target artifact.

cards.name: Adriana, Captain of the Guard
cards.text:
Melee (Whenever this creature attacks, it gets +1/+1 until end of turn for each opponent you attacked this combat.)
Other creatures you control have melee. (If a creature has multiple instances of melee, each triggers separately.)

cards.name: Assemble the Legion
cards.text: At the beginning of your upkeep, put a muster counter on Assemble the Legion. Then create a 1/1 red and white Soldier creature token with haste for each muster counter on Assemble the Legion.

cards.name: Boros Charm
cards.text:
Choose one -
• Boros Charm deals 4 damage to target player or planeswalker.
• Permanents you control gain indestructible until end of turn.
• Target creature gains double strike until end of turn.

cards.name: Culling Ritual
cards.text: Destroy each nonland permanent with mana value 2 or less. Add {B} or {G} for each permanent destroyed this way.
cards.flavor: "Your own frailty is your undoing. I am merely the one to expose it."

cards.name: Heroic Reinforcements
cards.text: Create two 1/1 white Soldier creature tokens. Until end of turn, creatures you control get +1/+1 and gain haste. (They can attack and {T} this turn.)
cards.flavor: Cries of anguish quickly spurred cries of action.

cards.name: Jor Kadeen, the Prevailer
cards.text:
First strike
Metalcraft - Creatures you control get +3/+0 as long as you control three or more artifacts.
cards.flavor: "As long as my hand holds a blade, there's hope for a pure Mirrodin once again."

cards.name: Merciless Eviction
cards.text:
Choose one -
• Exile all artifacts.
• Exile all creatures.
• Exile all enchantments.
• Exile all planeswalkers.

cards.name: Moldervine Reclamation
cards.text: Whenever a creature you control dies, you gain 1 life and draw a card.
cards.flavor:
"The heroes of the past nourish our spirits by their example-and nourish our crops by their decay."
-Jeddeg, philosopher of graves

cards.name: Mortify
cards.text: Destroy target creature or enchantment.
cards.flavor:
"Your debt is erased."
-Hilgur, Orzhov euthanist

cards.name: Putrefy
cards.text: Destroy target artifact or creature. It can't be regenerated.
cards.flavor:
"All matter, animate or not, rots when exposed to time. We merely speed up the process."
